SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 971
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Jamar Livingston on
being named to the All-TCCAA First Team.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize and
commend those successful student athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor
to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Jamar Livingston of Walters State
Community College, an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven
himself a formidable competitor on the basketball court; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Community College Athletic Association (TCCAA) recently
named Mr. Livingston to the All-TCCAA First Team in recognition of his excellence on the court
for Walters State Community College; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Livingston was fourth in the conference in points per game at 13.4,
making sixty-six 3-pointers and shooting 82 percent from the charity stripe; on the defensive
side, he had forty-seven steals; and
WHEREAS, Jamar Livingston epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he
has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
court; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Livingston's notable achievement is a source of great pride for his
family, his community, and Walters State Community College, and it is appropriate that we
recognize this accomplished athlete; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Jamar Livingston of
